{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, in k-fold CV, the dataset is divided into k subsets or folds.",
    "During the first iteration of k-fold CV, the data in the first fold k = 1 is set aside for testing, while the data from the other folds are employed for model training.",
    "In subsequent iterations, the testing fold shifts to the next one k = 2, and the remaining data continue to serve as the training set.",
    "This cycle repeats until all the folds have been used for testing.",
    "For more practical validation, we carried out model development in phase 1 and model testing in phase 2 as can be seen in Fig. 1."
  ]
}